ctor tim williams to star in the ad the trivago guy became an unexpected celebrity with some people noting his unbuttoned shirt and creepy vibe while others found his scruffy appearance and deep voice inexplicably sexy” trivago responded to the comments by launching a contest that invited people to give trivago guy a makeover the trivago guy inspired parodies fan fiction and a large gay following many commenters asked why trivago chose not to have the actor wear a belt according to the actor that was an accident unfortunately none of the belts fit the belt loops that i had on williams said i think that was probably the best break we could have gotten following the large response for the us trivago guy the company decided to create french and spanish trivago guys work environmentedit trivago states that it attempts to recruit tech and business employees that are willing to cross borders trivagos first employees were hired via skype interview from spain italy and canada and today  percent of its staff is recruited internationally the company operates with virtually no hierarchies or titles instead using a model called swarm intelligence it also does not have fixed working hours and offers employees a fourday surprise holiday each year and one month working in mallorca trivago states that it receives around  applicants per year employeesedit the average age of a trivago employee is  years old  and it has  nationalities working out of its main office the office space has flags lining the desks representing where each employee originates from new campusedit on february   trivago announced its plans to build a global campus in düsseldorf designed to accommodate over  people and be ready by  the sixstory building is being designed by sop architekten in düsseldorf the new campus will be built on the docks of kesselstraße in the düsseldorf media harbour close to the famous neuer zollhof buildings designed by frank gehry the campus will be accessible by public transportation as well as by bike lawsuitsedit in august  buckeye tree lodge and sequoia village inn llc filed a classaction lawsuit in california accusing the company and its partners of brazen deceit by coordinating with internet search engines and social media institutions to return false results on lodging entities in favor of those affiliated with their websites in violation of the lanham act the case is pending referencesedit  a b c d e f lead digital arbeiten bei trivago keine hierarchien und  biersorten gratis  grunderszene ranking  a b expedia inc expedia announces agreement to acquire majority of trivago  a b c d e f g h grunderszene trivago auf leisen sohlen  stellant partners howzat media invests in trivago the germanbased travel website focused on hotels reviews  community  grunderszene insight steigt zu millionenbewertung bei trivago ein  expedia to acquire stake in german hotel site reuters  retrieved    rp online mit  jahren den exit geschafft  anrej lehnert linkedin  a b c skift interview trivago building big team in shift toward directhotel relationships  a b c d e hospitality net trivago unveils plans for new global campus  skift trivago acquisition of hoteltech startup highlights evolution of booking sites  grunderszene mit altbier zu neuen startupvisionen  expedias hotel search service trivago plans ipo fortune retrieved    roof katie trivago closes up  in public debut techcrunch retrieved    trivago  expedia inc expedia inc retrieved    quora how much does trivago charge hotels per provision  hotel marketing trivago helps hotels manage online presence  hotel insight worried about how to optimse your hotel on ota websites trivago offer a helping hand  pulsoturistico trivago desembarca en argentina  a b mashable  apps to save you money  cnet trivago  the hotel search for android  usa today homeexchangecom wins best appwebsite for booking your stay  independent save time and money when booking your holiday with these handy apps  newscomau the  top apps to take o